<br>
And as far as priorities go, I would certainly lecture anyone who thought that spending at least 10 hours a day, 5 days a week on an online game is a worthwhile thing to do.  The same way I'd lecture anyone who spends the same amount of time in front of a TV, or a Playstation, or an Xbox.<br>
<br>
Think about it this way:  A plane crash-landed in the residential section of Queens.  Tornados and floods have wiped out entire towns and counties.  Drunk drivers and road rage have killed their share as well.  There are many other circumstances that occur beyond our control.  If you were unlucky enough to die at that moment, would you have died satisfied with yourself and your accomplishments?  Could you have spent a bit more time doing something far more meaningful?<br>
<br>
If you died today, right this very minute, would you have a long and inspiring obituary?  Or will it read, &quot;tried to get to level 50 ... Loading, please wait ...&quot;<br>
<br>
I don't expect to change anyone's belief or value system ... but I will make you think twice about them.<br>
