<br>
If you died today, right this very minute, would you have a long and inspiring obituary? Or will it read, &quot;tried to get to level 50 ... Loading, please wait ...&quot;<br>
&lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
I have a sneaking suspicion that you're spouting the above crap because you feel guilty about your own time spent online and you feel that preaching on a soapbox somehow removes you from the fact that you're as guilty as anyone else who frequents these or other EQ-related boards.<br>
<br>
...You don't have a carefully crafted signature with a link to an up-to-date character, so you're probably not as extreme as some others.. But you do have 225 posts on this board. ... <br>
Figure it takes you ten or more minutes to write a message (conservative estimate considering time spent reading the posts before it) ... Now I'm no math whiz, but that's 2250 minutes, right, which you might as well round off to 40 hours. ... You could probably easily double, triple that or more to account for the time you spend reading and refreshing.<br>
<br>
You'll probably protest that you do it at work, so it's not a waste of time ... ha! You could have spent that time writing a novel, researching or reading about something important and interesting, working on new skills, writing letters to loved ones, etc., etc...<br>
<br>
Now factor in your game time ... only you know what that is, but I'm guessing that anyone who is involved enough in the game to come to message boards plays at least 10 hours a week, probably much more. <br>
<br>
So unless you're coming here to say you've given up EQ entirely, including reading and posting on message boards, because you've moved on to &quot;something far more meaningful,&quot; then you are a hypocrite. <br>
<br>
No one wants to hear how much more in control of yourself you think you are than the rest of us. Why don't you just come back after you win that Pulitzer or invent that must-have technology and then we might be impressed.<br>
<br>
Until then ... kindly shut up.<br>
